  "title": "M&E Supervisor",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>  Duties &\nResponsibilities for M&E Supervisor</strong></u></p><p>1. Installing and maintaining, repairing building electrical&\nmechanical distribution systems</p><p>2. Monitor the operations and make customer approved adjustments of\nchilled water systems, heat exchangers, CRAC Units, HVAC, electrical systems, emergency back-up systems, hot water systems, pumps, valves, filters and other mechanical and electrical equipment</p><p>3. Installing outlets, disconnects, motor starters, inside and\noutside lighting systems, frequency drives, building safety equipment, fans,\npumps, and motors, and other electrical-related systems, fire alarm systems</p><p>4.Maintain and repair the mechanical, electrical, security and fire\nprotection systems that protect and support business critical information\nsystems (servers, mainframes, etc)</p><p>5. A working understanding of commercial three phase electrical\nsystems</p><p>6. Disassemble, clean, repair, and reassemble a variety of electrical\nappliances, controls and equipment following established procedures</p><p>7.Diagnose and correct malfunctions in interior and exterior\nelectrical circuits</p><p>8.   Test electrical equipment to identify and fix malfunctions</p><p>9.    \nAssist with job site and general safety, including general ground\nsupport, staging materials, and general site preparation and clean-up.</p><p>10. Ensure that all equipment stays in line with electrical codes,\nregulations, and standards</p><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><p>Diploma/Or equivalent\nand 2 years of experience in maintenance/repair or related field; or any\nequivalent combination of education, training, and experience.</p><p>1.    Two (2) years of HVAC experience preferably\nworking with chilled water systems, or a combination of training and work\nexperience.</p><p>2. Proficient in providing Building Services technical advice.</p><p>3.  Familiar with HVAC and building codes and standards</p><p>4. Extensive experience working across a variety of building\nprojects associated to industrial, commercial.</p>",
